Step 1: Create a Simple Application
Create a project folder:
mkdir docker-app
cd docker-app


Create an index.html file:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Hello Docker</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello, Docker! My first containerized application.</h1>
</body>
</html>

Step 2: Create a Dockerfile
Inside the same folder, create a file named Dockerfile:
# Use an official lightweight web server
FROM nginx:alpine

# Copy application code into Nginx default public directory
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

Step 3: Build the Docker Image
docker build -t my-docker-app . #my-docker-app → name of your image , . → means build using the current directory


Step 4: Run the Docker Container
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name my-container my-docker-app #-d → run in background ,-p 8080:80 → map localhost port 8080 → container port 80


Step 5: Test the Application

Open your browser: http://localhost:8080

You should see: Hello, Docker! My first containerized application.

Step 6: Check Running Containers
docker ps

Step 7: Stop and Remove Container (Optional)
docker stop my-container
docker rm my-container
